This paper deals with the problem of model selection in graphical models with latent variables, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper provides a transformational characterization of Markov equivalence for directed acyclic graphs with latent variables, which is a fundamental problem in graphical model inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory), which are all relevant to the topic of graphical models and model selection.
